@SP Typing speed (and, as P notes, reading speed) absolutely factors into solve speed. I grew up before the true digital natives but had to type up all my essays in college and grad school, which gave me years of experience both typing at pace and typing-while-reading-a-line-you're-quoting-from-a-printed-document. 

Crosswordwise, this has helped me gain the once-elusive skill of reading-the-next-clue-while-answering-the-last-one on my computer; my Monday best currently sits under 2-1/2 minutes and I solved today's puzzle in just over 5, which included some pauses to think through clues.

So yes, P.'s time is totally doable (and huge congrats, P., on the PB!). And I hope that amidst the chaos of this time, we all keep comparing ourselves to our own bests and just go from there.

