Mickey Mantle was a very well-known player for the New York Yankees baseball team in the 50s and 60s.  It was the gimme-est of gimmes for many New Yorkers, but I can see that it might be challenging for a Brit.  On the other hand, the number is five letters long, meaning it can only be THREE or SEVEN.  So that could be a major help for anyone who had no idea.

